
[1]avidity

   AVID'ITY, n. [L. aviditas, from avidus, and this from aveo, to desire,
   to have appetite; Heb. to desire, or covet.]

   1. Greediness; strong appetite; applied to the senses:

   2. Eagerness; intenseness of desire; applied to the mind.
